article.headline: Sam Houston St. 88, St. Gregory's 40
article.story: HUNTSVILLE, Texas (AP) -- Reggie Rawlins came off the bench to score 15 points as Sam Houston State defeated St. Gregory's 88-40 on Tuesday night. The Bearkats (3-0) jumped out to 12-0 lead and never trailed. Ryan Bright added 14 points and had nine rebounds for Sam Houston State. Shamir McDaniel scored 12 points and James Barrett had 11. Derek Washington led St. Gregory's (2-3) with nine points. Sam Houston State led 40-16 at the half. The Bearkats shot 55 percent from the field while St. Gregory's shot 29 percent.
